B. Accomplishments/Planned Programs ($ in Millions, Article Quantities in Each)                                                       FY 2025    FY 2026        FY 2027
provides strategic planning, requirements development, program coordination and integration, acquisition, financial management,
contracting, engineering, and program assessments for development and acquisition of space applications within MDA and
jointly with the Agencies and Services. In support of these future capabilities, SAMD also provides the MDSEA platform and
MDSC TIL for the experimentation, integration, and testing of current and future Missile Defense System Space Programs. A key
element of this research involves prototyping new sensor technologies, such as EBS applications, which are critically important for
Missile Defense System - Next in the fundamental application areas of tracking, engaging, and assessing missile threats. These
sensors are being sought to improve detection and guidance capabilities against sophisticated challenges, including hypersonic
and maneuverable missiles, across all phases of flight. As the enterprise ground segment solution for current and future missile
defense space missions, MDSEA is integral to this effort.

Recurring activities include:
- Technology maturation, including continuous algorithm development for tracking, typing, and discrimination against maneuvering
and hypersonic threats.
- Artificial Intelligence/Machine Language (AI/ML) modeling, leveraging neuromorphic processing techniques with evolving scene
simulations to improve performance.
- Requirements and capability integration of Missile Defense System - Next space capabilities into the Missile Defense System.
- Data processing and architecture evolution, focusing on the low-latency, high-volume sensor-to-ground pipeline and integration
with critical platforms like MDSEA.
- MDSC TIL enhancements to specifically support disruptive technology hardware-in-the-loop testing, advancing capabilities, and
overall systems testing.
- Test planning, execution and analysis support for United States Space Force (USSF) developed Space-based Interceptor (SBI).
- Performance analysis support.
- Demonstration enabling activity support.
- Demonstration planning and executing activity support.
- Coordination and execution with the USSF on development, integration, and test of Missile Defense System - Next space-based
capabilities through an Integrated Program Office in support of the President's Executive Order 14186.
- Space system engineering, integration, test planning, execution, and analysis of space capabilities across the agencies and
Services (PWSA and SBI).
- Acquisition, program execution, financial management, contracting, program protection/security, cost estimating, logistics and
mission assurance in support of space-based capabilities.
- MDSEA and MDSC operations and sustainment in support of Missile Defense System Space Programs.
- Build, develop and acquire Space Applications to support the 10 Steps to Ballistic Missile Intercept.
- Integration of space data with the Missile Defense System to enhance system capabilities.


